Total Winnings: $1,067,983 Games: Global Offensive Links History Created: : 2015-03-09 : 2015-06-19 Disbanded: 2022-06-04 Renegades was a professional gaming organization, founded in March 2015 under the name Misfits . Originally a League of Legends team, the organisation rebranded as Renegades on June 18, 2015, and picked up the former Vox Eminor roster for their own CS:GO squad. On August 30, 2016, Jonas Jerebko bought the organization from Christopher " MonteCristo " Mykles and Chris Badawi. [ 1 ] He is the third NBA player to publicly acquire a stake in an esports organization after Rick Fox ( Echo Fox ) and Shaquille O'Neal ( NRG Esports ). Contents 1 History 1.1 Timeline 2 Player Roster 2.1 Former 3 Organization 3.1 Active 3.2 Former 4 Results 5 Gallery 5.1 Rosters 6 References History [ edit ] See also: History of Renegades Timeline [ edit ] 2015 2016 2017 2018 2019 2020 2021 2022 Show All March 9th - Misfits is formed. June 18th - Misfits rebrands as Renegades . June 19th - Renegades sign the former Vox Eminor roster - Havoc , SPUNJ , jks , AZR and Yam join. [ 2 ] February 8th - USTILO joins, replacing Havoc who steps down from the active roster but remains as a substitute player. [ 3 ] February 21st - Havoc is picked up by Legacy eSports , alongside former teammate topguN . [ 4 ] April 23rd - Australian caster peekay joins as coach. June 17th - SPUNJ retires. [ 5 ] July 12th - Renegades signs Rickeh from Team Immunity . [ 6 ] January 4th - kassad replaces peekay as the coach of Renegades . [ 7 ] February 14th - Rickeh is benched, atter joins the team temporarily for DreamHack Las Vegas and ESL Pro League . [ 8 ] [ 9 ] March 6th - Rickeh officially leaves and joins Counter Logic Gaming . [ 10 ] March 23rd - yam leaves Renegades . [ 11 ] March 31st - Nifty transfers to Renegades from Selfless Gaming . [ 12 ] April 13th - Renegades announce their completed roster with the inclusion of nexa as their fifth player. [ 13 ] August 18th - Jayzwalkingz joins Renegades on a trial basis to replace nexa . [ 14 ] September 1st - Renegades acquire NAF from OpTic Gaming . [ 15 ] [ 16 ] February 5th - NAF departs Renegades for Team Liquid . [ 17 ] February 7th - jkaem joins Renegades . He later reveals that his initial contract is for six months. [ 18 ] [ 19 ] May 17th - kassad announces his departure from Renegades . [ 20 ] June 23rd - Ryu announces that he will be joining the team as a coach on trial. [ 21 ] September 24th - Ryu leaves Renegades . [ 22 ] September 27th - Nifty leaves to join Team Envy . [ 23 ] September 29th - USTILO is released from the organisation. [ 24 ] September 30th - liazz and Gratisfaction join the team. [ 25 ] October 8th - kassad returns to the team as coach. [ 26 ] [ 27 ] October 31st - 100 Thieves acquire Renegades ' roster. [ 28 ] December 3rd - Renegades acquire Grayhound Gaming 's roster. [ 29 ] January 8th - Renegades part ways with DickStacy . [ 30 ] January 12th - Renegades sign Hatz . [ 31 ] July 2nd - Renegades sign mithR as their head coach. [ 32 ] November 14th - mithR is acquired by mousesports to be their new coach. [ 33 ] February 10th - dexter is acquired by mousesports . [ 34 ] February 13th - Renegades sign aliStair . [ 35 ] June 30th - Renegades sign Kingfisher as head coach. [ 36 ] December 16th - Renegades part ways with malta . [ 37 ] February 13th - Renegades acquire Liazz from EXTREMUM . [ 38 ] June 4th - Renegades ' roster is acquired by ORDER .
